    "Apple and Amazon have their own opaque technologies, leaving users in the dark as to exactly why an app, story, or book is featured at a particular time or in a particular place.",
    "The secrecy is understandable as a business strategy, but it devastates our ability to understand the social world Silicon Valley is creating.",
    "Moreover, behind the technical inscrutability, there's plenty of room for opportunistic, exploitative, and just plain careless conduct to hide.\"",
